{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T7jNxLs6gWhDRp4pWq9aHS","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the complete contents of all 9 files:\n\n## 1. useEventSender.ts\nCustom React hook that manages event sending and seed data operations. Defines types for EventPayload, SendResult, and SeedResult. Includes:\n- `sendEvent()`: POSTs to /api/events with payload, tracks lastDeviceId\n- `sendSeed()`: POSTs to /api/seed, then fetches /api/seed/status for event count\n- `generateId()`: Helper that creates 8-character random IDs\n- State management for loading and lastDeviceId\n\n## 2. QuickFireButtons.tsx\nClient component rendering 5 pre-configured event buttons:\n- Anonymous Page View: generates new device_id, page=\"/home\"\n- Button Click: reuses lastDeviceId or generates new one\n- Identify User: sends device_id + TEST_USER_ID (\"test@example.com\")\n- Purchase: sends user_id + amount/currency properties\n- Signup: generates new device_id and unique user_id\nEach button shows success/error feedback below it\n\n## 3. CustomEventForm.tsx\nCollapsible form for creating custom events. Fields:\n- Event Name (required)\n- Device ID (optional)\n- User ID (optional)\n- Timestamp (optional, datetime-local input)\n- Properties (optional, parsed JSON)\nValidates JSON properties in real-time, disables submit if invalid. Shows success/error feedback after submission.\n\n## 4. SeedDataButton.tsx\nSimple button component that calls sendSeed(). While loading, shows CircularProgress spinner. After completion, displays event count formatted with locale string or error message.\n\n## 5. page.tsx\nTest page layout at /test. Uses grid layout (1 column on mobile, 2 on desktop):\n- Left panel: Event Sender containing QuickFireButtons, CustomEventForm, and SeedDataButton\n- Right panel: Live Feed placeholder (coming soon)\n\n## 6. useEventSender.test.ts\nComprehensive test suite using Vitest. Tests:\n- Initial state (lastDeviceId null, loading false)\n- sendEvent: payload formatting, HTTP responses (201, 400, 409, 500), lastDeviceId tracking\n- sendSeed: POST to /api/seed, status fetch, error handling, network failures\n- Loading state transitions\n\n## 7. QuickFireButtons.test.tsx\nTests all 5 buttons rendering and their payloads:\n- Anonymous Page View generates device_id and page property\n- Button Click reuses device_id from previous event\n- Identify User sends device_id + test@example.com\n- Purchase sends correct amount/currency\n- Signup generates unique device_id and user_id each time\nTests success/error feedback display\n\n## 8. CustomEventForm.test.tsx\nTests form visibility toggle, field validation:\n- Submit button disabled until event_name is filled\n- JSON validation for properties field\n- Payload construction with optional fields\n- Success/error feedback display\n- Device ID, User ID, and parsed properties included when provided\n\n## 9. SeedDataButton.test.tsx\nTests button click triggering sendSeed:\n- Button disabled during loading\n- Result displays with formatted event count (12,000 format)\n- Error message shown on failure\n- Container has correct data-testid"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"64f77740-6e45-45b6-8c03-7f0c13981bf2","uuid":"e2539b82-9be4-4544-989f-8a505c1c32c6","timestamp":"2026-04-15T17:59:58.112Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the following files and return their full contents:\n1. /Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/test/useEventSender.ts\n2. /Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/test/QuickFireButtons.tsx\n3. /Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/test/CustomEventForm.tsx\n4. /Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/test/SeedDataButton.tsx\n5. /Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/test/page.tsx\n6. /Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-nigh