{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01V4NCqH2k3vameMyzvWZk6F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All Phase B HTTP checks pass. Now let me write the eval file. Let me also check whether e2e tests are warranted - the plan mentions Playwright infrastructure exists. Let me check.\n\nThe plan says:\n- **Integration gap**: HTTP checks for `/test` page rendering — requires dev server\n\nThose have been covered by my HTTP checks in Phase B. The plan's integration gap was specifically about HTTP checks for the `/test` page rendering, which I've now verified.\n\nFor e2e tests: The plan mentions Playwright is installed. This feature introduces a new page with significant UI interactions. However, since this is sprint 1 and the draft already covers all sprint contract criteria, and since the HTTP checks (the only integration gap mentioned) are covered, I should check whether to write e2e tests.\n\n\nThe HTTP checks cover the integration gap mentioned in the plan, and since the page relies on client-side React with mocked fetch calls rather than a real ClickHouse backend, I'll skip the e2e tests and move on to writing the eval file with all criteria passing.\n\nNow I'm verifying the sprint contract results—typecheck, lint, and build all pass cleanly, tests show 454 passing with no failures, and all four required components exist and export correctly.\n\nThe test page imports all three components and renders them with the expected test IDs, so everything checks out for a full 10/10 approval. The live feed placeholder is intentional per the plan, and e2e tests weren't part of this sprint's scope.\n\nThe HTTP validation requirements from the plan are being handled by Phase B checks, and those pre-existing lint warnings in the seed test file aren't related to what I'm building here.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":156,"cache_read_input_tokens":54971,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":156},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"64f77740-6e45-45b6-8c03-7f0c13981bf2","uuid":"67ea5272-20ac-4d23-b6df-e56fb12c7e57"}
